summary: This is a calendar entry for the start of jury selection (voir dire) in the Ghislaine Maxwell trial, scheduled for November 16-20, 2021, at the 40 Foley Square Courthouse in New York. It lists various government and contractor attendees involved in the trial proceedings.

events.title: Maxwell Trial Jury Selection Begins
events.description: Start of the voir dire process for jury selection in the criminal trial of Ghislaine Maxwell.

events.title: Maxwell Trial Jury Selection Scheduled End
events.description: Scheduled end date for the jury selection phase of the Ghislaine Maxwell trial.

locations: 40 Foley Courthouse (40 Foley Square Courthouse, New York, NY)
keyFacts: Jury selection for Ghislaine Maxwell's trial was scheduled to begin on November 16, 2021.
The event was organized by the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York (USANYS).
Attendees listed include representatives from the FBI, NYPD, and multiple contractors.
The trial proceedings were to take place at the 40 Foley Square Courthouse in New York.
This document is a calendar entry created on May 11, 2021, detailing the logistics for a key phase of the trial.
